wiki.summary: On “One Take,“ the lead track off of True 2 Myself, Lil Tjay raps about his newfound fame and the repercussions that came along with it. Tjay uses references to expensive clothing and weaponry to flex his newfound fame, whilst also reminiscing about his life prior to his fame and wealth. The piano-filled beat for the track was smoothly produced and handled by first-time collaborator of Tjay’s, ZiggyOnTheKeyboard. Tjay also performed this track live at Genius' Open Mic studios on October 15 Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: On “One Take,“ the lead track off of True 2 Myself, Lil Tjay raps about his newfound fame and the repercussions that came along with it. Tjay uses references to expensive clothing and weaponry to flex his newfound fame, whilst also reminiscing about his life prior to his fame and wealth. The piano-filled beat for the track was smoothly produced and handled by first-time collaborator of Tjay’s, ZiggyOnTheKeyboard. Tjay also performed this track live at Genius' Open Mic studios on October 15, 2019, four days after the track’s official release. Read more on Last.fm.
